[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6589,
        "end_time": 8249,
        "text": "You heard the traveler&#39;s tales,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 8249,
        "end_time": 10029,
        "text": "you followed the crumbling maps,"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 10029,
        "end_time": 12899,
        "text": "and now, after a long and dangerous quest,"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 12899,
        "end_time": 16024,
        "text": "you have some good news and some bad news."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 16024,
        "end_time": 19469,
        "text": "The good news is you&#39;ve managed to locate\nthe legendary dungeon"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 19469,
        "end_time": 22661,
        "text": "containing the stash \nof ancient Stygian coins"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 22661,
        "end_time": 25595,
        "text": "and the eccentric wizard \nwho owns the castle"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 25595,
        "end_time": 29244,
        "text": "has even generously\nagreed to let you have them."
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 29244,
        "end_time": 31964,
        "text": "The bad news is that he&#39;s not\nquite as generous"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 31964,
        "end_time": 37703,
        "text": "about letting you leave the dungeon,\nunless you solve his puzzle."
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 37703,
        "end_time": 39683,
        "text": "The task sounds simple enough."
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 39683,
        "end_time": 44284,
        "text": "Both faces of each coin bear\nthe fearsome scorpion crest,"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 44284,
        "end_time": 45373,
        "text": "one in silver,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 45373,
        "end_time": 47113,
        "text": "one in gold."
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 47113,
        "end_time": 50844,
        "text": "And all you have to do is separate them\ninto two piles"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 50844,
        "end_time": 56294,
        "text": "so that each has the same number\nof coins facing silver side up."
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 56294,
        "end_time": 60305,
        "text": "You&#39;re about to begin when all\nof the torches suddenly blow out"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 60305,
        "end_time": 62943,
        "text": "and you&#39;re left in total darkness."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 62943,
        "end_time": 65022,
        "text": "There are hundreds \nof coins in front of you"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 65022,
        "end_time": 68756,
        "text": "and each one feels the same on both sides."
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 68756,
        "end_time": 71602,
        "text": "You try to remember \nwhere the silver-facing coins were,"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 71602,
        "end_time": 73273,
        "text": "but it&#39;s hopeless."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 73273,
        "end_time": 74771,
        "text": "You&#39;ve lost track."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 74771,
        "end_time": 77141,
        "text": "But you do know one thing for certain."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 77141,
        "end_time": 78612,
        "text": "When there was still light,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 78612,
        "end_time": 83382,
        "text": "you counted exactly \n20 silver-side-up coins in the pile."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 83382,
        "end_time": 84842,
        "text": "What can you do?"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 84842,
        "end_time": 89437,
        "text": "Are you doomed to remain in the dungeon\nwith your newfound treasure forever?"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 89437,
        "end_time": 91529,
        "text": "You&#39;re tempted to kick the pile of coins"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 91529,
        "end_time": 94892,
        "text": "and curse the curiosity \nthat brought you here."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 94892,
        "end_time": 97302,
        "text": "But at the last moment, you stop yourself."
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 97302,
        "end_time": 101815,
        "text": "You just realized there&#39;s \na surprisingly easy solution."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 101815,
        "end_time": 103463,
        "text": "What is it?"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 103463,
        "end_time": 106763,
        "text": "Pause here if you want to figure\nit out for yourself."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 106763,
        "end_time": 107793,
        "text": "Answer in: 3"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 107793,
        "end_time": 109163,
        "text": "Answer in: 2"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 109163,
        "end_time": 110893,
        "text": "Answer in: 1"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 110893,
        "end_time": 114185,
        "text": "You carefully move aside 20 coins\none by one."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 114185,
        "end_time": 117775,
        "text": "It doesn&#39;t matter which ones:\nany coins will do,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 117775,
        "end_time": 120323,
        "text": "and then flip each one of them over."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 120323,
        "end_time": 122063,
        "text": "That&#39;s all there is to it."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 122063,
        "end_time": 124505,
        "text": "Why does such a simple solution work?"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 124505,
        "end_time": 128044,
        "text": "Well, it doesn&#39;t matter how many\ncoins there are to start with."
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 128044,
        "end_time": 132924,
        "text": "What matters is that only 20\nof the total are facing silver side up."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 132924,
        "end_time": 135503,
        "text": "When you take 20 coins in the darkness,"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 135503,
        "end_time": 139088,
        "text": "you have no way of knowing how many\nof these silver-facing coins"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 139088,
        "end_time": 141947,
        "text": "have ended up in your new pile."
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 141947,
        "end_time": 144274,
        "text": "But let&#39;s suppose you got 7 of them."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 144274,
        "end_time": 147715,
        "text": "This means that there are 13\nsilver-facing coins left"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 147715,
        "end_time": 149606,
        "text": "in the original pile."
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 149606,
        "end_time": 153215,
        "text": "It also means that the other\n13 coins in your new pile"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 153215,
        "end_time": 155796,
        "text": "are facing gold side up."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 155796,
        "end_time": 160500,
        "text": "So what happens when you flip\nall of the coins in the new pile over?"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 160500,
        "end_time": 164771,
        "text": "Seven gold-facing coins and\n13 silver-facing coins"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 164771,
        "end_time": 167995,
        "text": "to match the ones in the original pile."
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 167995,
        "end_time": 172930,
        "text": "It turns out this works no matter how\nmany of the silver-facing coins you grab,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 172930,
        "end_time": 175930,
        "text": "whether it&#39;s all of them, \na few, or none at all."
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 176521,
        "end_time": 180515,
        "text": "That&#39;s because of what&#39;s known\nas complementary events."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 180515,
        "end_time": 184227,
        "text": "We know that each coin only has\ntwo possible options."
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 184227,
        "end_time": 188476,
        "text": "If it&#39;s not facing silver side up,\nit must be gold side up,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 188476,
        "end_time": 189847,
        "text": "and vice versa,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 189847,
        "end_time": 192117,
        "text": "and in any combination of 20 coins,"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 192117,
        "end_time": 195289,
        "text": "the number of gold-facing\nand silver-facing coins"
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 195289,
        "end_time": 197777,
        "text": "must add up to 20."
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 197777,
        "end_time": 200927,
        "text": "We can prove this mathematically\nusing algebra."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 200927,
        "end_time": 204498,
        "text": "The number of silver-facing coins\nremaining in the original pile"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 204498,
        "end_time": 209167,
        "text": "will always be 20 minus\nhowever many you moved to the new pile."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 209167,
        "end_time": 212517,
        "text": "And since your new pile also\nhas a total of 20 coins,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 212517,
        "end_time": 215257,
        "text": "its number of gold-facing coins will be"
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 215257,
        "end_time": 219487,
        "text": "20 minus the amount of \nsilver-facing coins you moved."
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 219487,
        "end_time": 222318,
        "text": "When all the coins in the new pile\nare flipped,"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 222318,
        "end_time": 225966,
        "text": "these gold-facing coins become\nsilver-facing coins,"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 225966,
        "end_time": 231538,
        "text": "so now the number of silver-facing\ncoins in both piles is the same."
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 231538,
        "end_time": 235159,
        "text": "The gate swings open\nand you hurry away with your treasure"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 235159,
        "end_time": 237268,
        "text": "before the wizard changes his mind."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 237268,
        "end_time": 240877,
        "text": "At the next crossroads, you flip\none of your hard-earned coins"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 240880,
        "end_time": 243800,
        "text": "to determine the way \nto your next adventure."
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 243800,
        "end_time": 247350,
        "text": "But before you go, we have another \nquick coin riddle for you \u2013"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 247350,
        "end_time": 251549,
        "text": "one that comes from this video \nsponsor\u2019s excellent website."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 251549,
        "end_time": 254010,
        "text": "Here we have 8 arrangements of coins."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 254010,
        "end_time": 258790,
        "text": "You can flip over adjacent pairs of coins \nas many times as you like."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 258790,
        "end_time": 262919,
        "text": "A flip always changes gold to silver, \nand silver to gold."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 262919,
        "end_time": 266176,
        "text": "Can you figure out how to tell, \nat a glance,"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 266176,
        "end_time": 269636,
        "text": "which arrangements can be made all gold?"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 269636,
        "end_time": 273916,
        "text": "You can try an interactive version of \nthis puzzle and confirm your solution"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 273916,
        "end_time": 276296,
        "text": "on Brilliant\u2019s website."
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 276296,
        "end_time": 279386,
        "text": "We love Brilliant.org because the site \ngives you tools"
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 279386,
        "end_time": 282916,
        "text": "to approach problem-solving in \none of our favorite ways\u2014"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 282916,
        "end_time": 287228,
        "text": "by breaking puzzles into smaller pieces \nor limited cases,"
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 287228,
        "end_time": 289648,
        "text": "and working your way up from there."
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 289648,
        "end_time": 292928,
        "text": "This way, you&#39;re building up a \nframework for problem solving,"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 292928,
        "end_time": 295728,
        "text": "instead of just memorizing formulas."
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 295728,
        "end_time": 299308,
        "text": "You can sign up for Brilliant for free, \nand if you like riddles"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 299308,
        "end_time": 302783,
        "text": "a Brilliant.org premium membership \nwill get you access"
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 302783,
        "end_time": 305794,
        "text": "to countless more interactive puzzles."
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 305794,
        "end_time": 309636,
        "text": "Try it out today by visiting \nbrilliant.org\/TedEd"
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 309636,
        "end_time": 312528,
        "text": "and use that link so they know \nwe sent you."
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 312528,
        "end_time": 315887,
        "text": "The first 833 of you to visit that link"
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 315887,
        "end_time": 320457,
        "text": "will receive 20% off the annual premium \nsubscription fee."
    }
]